==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lining
<hw>Lin"ing</hw> <pr>(l⟦imac⟧n"⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Line</er> to cover the in side.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of
one who lines; the act or process of making lines, or of inserting a
lining.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which covers the inner surface of anything, as
of a garment or a box; also, the contents of anything.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>lining</qex> of his coffers shall make coats⟦br⟧
To deck our soldiers.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Link</ent>⟦br⟧
